      <section eId="sec_1" class="prov1">
        <heading>“Appropriate consent” to adult transplant activities</heading>
        <num>1.</num>
        <subsection class="prov2">
          <num>(1)</num>
          <content>
            <p>Section 3 of the Human Tissue Act 2004 (<def ukl:startQuote="“" ukl:endQuote="”">appropriate consent</def>: adults) is amended in accordance with subsections (2) to (5).</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection class="prov2">
          <num>(3)</num>
          <content>
            <p><mod>After subsection (6A), insert regular para1s—<quotedStructure startQuote="“" endQuote="”" ukl:indent="indent0" ukl:context="body" ukl:docName="nia"><level class="para1"><num>(a)</num><content><p>the storage of the body of a deceased person for use for the purpose of transplantation;</p></content></level><level class="para1"><num>(d)</num><content><p>the use for the purpose of transplantation of any permitted material which has come from a human body.</p></content></level></quotedStructure><inline name="AppendText">.</inline></mod></p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection class="prov2">
          <num>(4)</num>
          <content>
            <p><mod>Subparas—<quotedStructure startQuote="“" endQuote="”" ukl:indent="indent0" ukl:context="body" ukl:docName="nia"><level class="para2"><num>(i)</num><content><p>the storage of the body of a deceased person for use for the purpose of transplantation;</p></content></level><level class="para2"><num>(ii)</num><content><p>the use for the purpose of transplantation of any permitted material which has come from a human body.</p></content></level></quotedStructure><inline name="AppendText">.</inline></mod></p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection class="prov2">
          <num>(5)</num>
          <content>
            <p><mod>Lone para with (i) is para1—<quotedStructure startQuote="“" endQuote="”" ukl:indent="indent0" ukl:context="body" ukl:docName="nia"><level class="para2"><num>(i)</num><content><p>the storage of the body of a deceased person for use for the purpose of transplantation;</p></content></level></quotedStructure><inline name="AppendText" /></mod></p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection class="prov2">
          <num>(6)</num>
          <content>
            <p><mod>Lone para with (ii) is para2—<quotedStructure startQuote="“" endQuote="”" ukl:indent="indent0" ukl:context="body" ukl:docName="nia"><level class="para2"><num>(ii)</num><content><p>the storage of the body of a deceased person for use for the purpose of transplantation;</p></content></level></quotedStructure><inline name="AppendText" /></mod></p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection class="prov2">
          <num>(7)</num>
          <content>
            <p><mod>Subparas non-consecutive—<quotedStructure startQuote="“" endQuote="”" ukl:indent="indent0" ukl:context="body" ukl:docName="nia"><level class="para2"><num>(xiv)</num><content><p>the storage of the body of a deceased person for use for the purpose of transplantation;</p></content></level><level class="para2"><num>(iix)</num><content><p>the use for the purpose of transplantation of any permitted material which has come from a human body.</p></content></level></quotedStructure><inline name="AppendText">.</inline></mod></p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection class="prov2">
          <num>(8)</num>
          <content>
            <p><mod>paras starting with roman numeral-like—<quotedStructure startQuote="“" endQuote="”" ukl:indent="indent0" ukl:context="body" ukl:docName="nia"><level class="para1"><num>(i)</num><content><p>the storage of the body of a deceased person for use for the purpose of transplantation;</p></content></level><level class="para1"><num>(j)</num><content><p>the use for the purpose of transplantation of any permitted material which has come from a human body.</p></content></level></quotedStructure><inline name="AppendText">.</inline></mod></p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection class="prov2">
          <num>(8)</num>
          <content>
            <p><mod>paras starting with roman numeral-like with children—<quotedStructure startQuote="“" endQuote="”" ukl:indent="indent0" ukl:context="body" ukl:docName="nia"><level class="para1"><num>(i)</num><intro><p>the storage of the body of a deceased person for use for the purpose of transplantation;</p></intro><level class="para2"><num>(i)</num><content><p>record their own decisions about transplantation after their death of parts of their body, or body.</p></content></level></level><level class="para1"><num>(j)</num><content><p>the use for the purpose of transplantation of any permitted material which has come from a human body.</p></content></level></quotedStructure><inline name="AppendText">.</inline></mod></p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
